text: Enjoyed talking to the media today about how we’re going to win this Senate seat. Got some new polling data this morning that shows us leading the democratic field. Let’s flip the Senate this November! #gapol
Making a difference starts today. I am proud to have qualified for the special election in Georgia, and I look forward to flipping the Senate blue.
Excited to officially be a #QUALIFIED candidate in Georgia’s Special Election! Fired up to continue on this next leg of the journey. Let’s turn Georgia blue! #FliptheSenate #gapol #bluewave2020
Well-said.
Happy Birthday to this great guy, great dad, super granddad, and role model for public service.  Much love on your 78th birthday.
Had a great night talking with the Cherokee County Democrats at their meeting this week!
It was great to speak with the Gwinnett High School Democrats this morning! Love to see young folks in GA energized about the election!
Great night to gather with friends and talk about my run for Senate!
It was an honor to speak at the Rabun County Democrats meeting earlier this week. I love seeing so many Georgians ready to fight and WIN this November! Let's do this!
The GOP has served up some high quality candidates for this race: the Trump kiss-up and the fake farmer. Actually, the fake farmer is also a Trump kiss-up.

Trump’s pollster released a poll this morning that puts me at the front of this race — BY A LOT. This proves not only that Democrats can win in Georgia, but that I am the first choice among voters in this state. I’m feeling energized and ready to flip Georgia blue.
What a great night with the UGA Young Democrats! Some great students with excellent questions out here in Athens. It makes me proud to see so many future leaders here in Georgia.
Had a great meeting this afternoon with Mayor Kelly Girtz!
Grabbing a quick bite to eat before heading to the Young Democrats of UGA meeting!
Excited to be here in the Classic City!
Thanks to everyone who has liked our page!
‪Doug Collins is running for Senate with the approval of one person in mind: Donald Trump. I’m running for no one’s approval but yours. ‬
‪#WeRemember #HolocaustMemorialDay #NeverAgain‬

I'd like to extend a "thank you" to Ted Terry for the important work that he did while running for Senate here in Georgia. It takes great courage to run for public office, and the road is certainly not an easy one -- even in your favorite pair of Chucks. Ted, I know you'll keep doing great things here in Georgia.

Excited to be speaking at YDUGA this Wednesday! If you're in the Athens area come on down!Join us this Wednesday at our weekly meeting to hear from US Senate Candidate Matt Lieberman! We will meet in MLC 248 and have free pizza. Come out and bring a friend and enjoy getting caught up on the news with other young Dems!

These numbers speak for themselves: Trump rubs the American public the wrong way -- and Georgia is not immune. According to a recent AJC poll, 57% of female voters and 87% of African American voters strongly disapprove of the way Trump is handling his job. The stage is set to flip Georgia blue, take back the Senate, and bring honesty and integrity back to Washington. We have a little over 10 months to knock doors, register voters, get out the vote, and go win.

The citizens of our nation's capital pay taxes, serve in the military, and contribute to the well being of the entire United States. That is why I am proud to stand with them and sign the #DCStatehoodPledge -- to bring the rights that every American deserves to the citizens of Washington, DC! Students for D.C. Statehood

Strong words from my law school friend, Michael Bennet, on the anniversary of the Citizens United decision. Couldn't have said it better myself.A decade after the Supreme Court decided the Citizens United case, the damage is clear: a flood of dark money, Republicans paralyzed on climate and gun violence because of wealthy special interests, corruption on the rise.  We can't wait another decade to overturn this terrible decision. Let's get to work.

With the first day of the impeachment trial underway, I urge my future Senate colleagues across the aisle to conduct a fair trial where the focus is on the facts -- not political pandering. The American people deserve to hear directly from the witnesses, and if President Trump really did nothing wrong then he should have nothing to worry about.

"I have decided to stick with love. Hate is too great a burden to bear." - Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Dr. King was a visionary, and it was his example of inspiring a nation with love and light that mark him as a unique, great leader in American history. It is my hope that as a nation we will honor Dr. King's memory and his words by making the effort to see through the lens of love, and leave hatred behind.

As Kelly Loeffler is sworn in today as a juror in the Senate trial of Donald J. Trump, she should remember she's taking an oath to God -- not Trump. Yes, there's a difference.  As a devout person, she should keep in mind that she's swearing to God her impartiality in this case. Unfortunately,  here's what she’s already said: “I can tell you with certainty my first vote is an easy one… I will stand strongly against impeachment and vote no." -Kelly Loeffler This looks like another conflict of interest for Loeffler -- between God and Trump.  And it looks like she's already picked Trump.   Add to this her getting a seat on the very Senate committee that regulates her husband's multi-billion dollar company...Conflict Kelly is off to a good start.

Today would have been the 91st birthday of Rev. Martin Luther King, Jr. His fearless leadership and dedication to civil rights made our country a more just and equal place. There is still much work to do, but his contributions towards making our country a more perfect union are unparalleled. We honor a true American hero today.

Sad to see Cory Booker end his campaign today. He is truly a fighter for truth and a leader of the highest character. I wish him well in the Senate, look forward to seeing him there, and thank him for his courage to run.

Kelly Loeffler, Jeff Sprecher, and the Republicans want to sweep this  massive conflict of interest under the rug. This is why I am running for Senate. Because the people of Georgia, and our country, deserve to be represented by honesty and integrity -- not senators who use their power to benefit themselves.

Thanks to the generous contributions of well over a THOUSAND Georgia residents across 180 cities and towns I am proud to announce that this campaign has raised over $700,000! I am extremely encouraged by not only the traction this campaign is getting, but by the traction Democrats are getting all over the South. Democrats just turned two Southern states blue in Kentucky and Virginia, and now our people-powered campaign is going to do the same in Georgia. Let's flip the Senate! #turngeorgiablue #gapol #bluewave2020 #FlipItBlue #NewYearBlueYear

Had a great evening with the American Jewish Committee at City Springs! I am proud to be a part of the Jewish community here in Georgia alongside over 2,000 metro-Atlanta community members as we stand up to intolerance and hate.Thank you to everyone who joined the Atlanta Jewish community and its allies for an incredible evening of solidarity last night. Atlanta will always remain #JewishandProud.
New Years resolutions for 2020: flip Georgia, take back the Senate, and take back the White House. All we have to do is vote. #NYE #2020resolutions #gapol

We've worked hard over the past few months and raised a lot of money, but the real work is only just beginning. Let's close out 2019 with a bang! Any amount that you can pitch in to help us reach our end-of-quarter goal is much appreciated. Contribute here:
Kelly Loeffler thinks she can buy this seat -- but she's wrong. It's the people of Georgia, not mega-donors, who will decide who they want representing them.

I read this morning the uplifting news about the Newtown High School football team winning the state championship on the anniversary of the Sandy Hook shooting. The people of Newtown have demonstrated over and over the resilience of the human spirit, and it’s inspiring to see the work that they’ve put in over the years to put an end to gun violence in America. #SandyHookPromise #everytown #gapol

The fact that Georgia politicians have been arguing over whether to appoint a Wall Street market maker or a far-right DC insider is a prime example of why Georgians are fed up with politics. That’s a bad way to pick a Senator, and it’s why the one we’re ending up with is so out-of-touch with Georgia families.  A Wall Street insider who bought the New York Stock Exchange is not who Georgia families need representing them in Washington.  I’m running for U.S. Senate because Georgians deserve a Senator who will lower the cost of healthcare, protect Roe v. Wade, and stand up to the NRA - in other words, someone who actually represents them.

Raise your hand if you've paid more in taxes last year than one of the biggest and richest companies in the United States. Whichever way you spin it, this practice is wrong. The wealth gap in America has been widening since the 1980s, and thanks to recent legislation, working class Americans are paying a much higher tax rate than some of the richest individuals in the nation. The facts don't lie: it's time for a change.

So proud that we were able to host a debate in Georgia. This state isn't just changing. It's already changed thanks to the incredible work of activists, local parties, and leaders like Stacey Abrams that have helped register over a million voters since 2016. 2020 is the year we flip Georgia blue! #FlipItBlue #gapol
Today is the deadline for all interested candidates to apply for Johnny Isakson's seat! I can't wait to find out who I'll be beating in November 2020. #MondayMotivation
I mourn the lives lost at Saugus High School. According to the Gun Violence Archive, there have been 38 school shootings over the course of one year. How can we continue to do nothing?

It's approaching freezing in Atlanta, and thanks to the Arctic Blast states all across the Midwest and the East Coast are feeling record cold temperatures. But if the Earth is getting warmer, why is it so cold?! Unseasonably cold weather is actually one of the hallmarks of climate change. Just an FYI, you know, in case someone's bothering you.
Thank you to all the servicemembers who have sacrificed for this country. We will be forever grateful for what you've done to keep us all safe and free. #VeteransDay

There is now a blue majority in every branch of government in Virginia and we just elected a democratic governor in Kentucky. The #BlueWave is growing and becoming a #BlueTsunami! We can win not one but TWO senate seats in Georgia next year. Let’s take back the Senate! #gapol #FlipItBlue

Sad and angry to see the Jewish community in America yet again targeted by a hateful person hoping to do us harm. I commend the authorities who were able to stop this vile, anti-semitic attack from taking place.  Hate's not new, and it's not going anywhere.  Love isn't new either, and we need more of it.  Along with vigilance.  It's my hope that we're witnessing the death throes of this resurgence of bigotry in America.

Great to hear from all of the talented and inspirational speakers at Big Brothers Big Sisters. I know the impact that programs like this can have. After law school I was the founding executive director of a local chapter of the "I Have A Dream" program because I saw what a huge impact mentorship and hope can have in shaping young lives. I was honored to attend and can't wait to support good work like this from Washington!

GA GOP seem very excited to purge voters.  Not so excited to add them.  Voters are purged by the hundreds of thousands, but only added one at a time. Recently, a study showed that in Ohio 20 percent of the voters purged should NOT have been removed from the voter rolls. At that rate in GA, it would mean that 60,000 voters are about to be disenfranchised. This is wrong and one of the many reasons I support a Voting Rights Act for the 21st century.

The road to the Senate leads through Georgia. I know through the progress of Stacey Abrams and the Democrats before me this state is absolutely flippable. Fired up and ready to turn Georgia Blue! #MondayMotivation

Senator Leroy Johnson was a force to be reckoned with and an icon of the civil rights movement. His important work is still celebrated today and should never be forgotten. We all owe a debt to this true public servant -- he will be missed, but his legacy will live on forever.
Glad to see President Carter on the road to recovery. Looking forward to seeing him get back to all the important work he is doing!
Enjoying this beautiful Georgia day with Disney! I hope you’ve all been enjoying this fall weather as much as we have.

Last night's dinner with the DPG was inspirational, and a testament to how much the party is growing. The numbers in 2018 were proof that Democrats in Georgia are primed to win valuable seats this cycle. 2018 was truly the year of the #BlueWave and this year we will be the year of the #BlueTsunami. Let's vote Blue! #GaPol
Excited to attend the DPG annual fundraising dinner this evening. It is always a pleasure to go out and support the state and local parties. #FlipItBlue #GaPol

Congratulations to astronauts Christina Koch and Jessica Meir for conducting the first all-female spacewalk! You are truly leaders in your field, and I know you will serve as an inspiration for the next generation of women in STEM.

America has lost a strong and compassionate leader with the passing of Rep. Elijah Cummings. He blessed this country with his integrity and his spirit of service. My condolences and the condolences of the Lieberman family are with Congressman Cummings' family today. #RIPElijahCummings

We made a video spoofing Kemp's infamous gun/boyfriend ad. I’m running for the U.S. Senate in Georgia to protect a woman’s right to choose, to fight voter suppression, and to ban assault weapons. #GApol Contribute here: https://secure.actblue.com/donate/lieberman-om?refcode=101619FB
Rain or shine, we have Pride! Had a great time marching in #atlpride2019 #LiebermanforSenate #gapol

The destruction and loss of civilian lives in Syria right now is a direct result of Trump's decision to betray our Kurdish allies. Mere hours after Turkey's invasion, two men connected to Trump's personal attorney and his Biden investigation were arrested on campaign finance charges. The time to act is NOW. With your support in 2020, we can flip the Senate and hold those responsible for this blight on our democracy accountable.
Wishing all who observe a meaningful Yom Kippur and an easy fast.
Disney might be looking for the treat in my hand, but the real treat has been all the support we’ve already received from you. Thank you, so much. Let’s do this!  #LiebermanForSenate

Had a great interview with Steven Fowler yesterday at GPB NPR! Give it a read with the link below #LiebermanForSenate  https://www.gpbnews.org/post/matt-lieberman-first-democrat-enter-race-isaksons-senate-seat

First official day campaigning and it’s great to settle into a new office! But what makes it even better is that this office is in Braves Country. Welcome to HQ at The Battery! #ChopOn #LiebermanforSenate

Today I announced my campaign for the U.S. Senate in Georgia. Like many Georgians across our great state, I’m fed up with the cynicism of politicians and the hatred and division in Washington. Enough is enough. I’m running for the U.S. Senate to challenge a broken Washington and to start getting things done for the people of Georgia. I hope you’ll join me today as we launch this effort to reclaim the country we love and all its greatness. Become a founding supporter today: https://liebermanforsenate.com
